  "prompt": "How much, if at all, will cotton khakis shrink when washed?",
  "response": "The shrinkage of cotton khakis depends on several factors:\n\n1. Pre-shrunk status:\n- If the khakis are labeled \"pre-shrunk,\" they will shrink minimally (around 1-3%)\n- If not pre-shrunk, they may shrink up to 5% in length and width\n\n2. Washing and drying conditions:\n- Hot water and high heat dryer settings cause more shrinkage\n- Warm or cold water and low heat settings minimize shrinkage\n- Line drying can help prevent significant shrinking\n\n3. Fabric composition:\n- 100% cotton khakis tend to shrink more\n- Cotton blends (with polyester or spandex) shrink less\n\nTypical shrinkage ranges:\n- Length: 1-3%\n- Waist: 1-2%\n\nTo minimize shrinkage:\n- Wash in cold water\n- Use low heat or air dry\n- Follow care label instructions\n\nIf you're concerned about fit, consider buying a slightly larger size or having them professionally pre-shrunk.",
